On Thu, 11 Nov 1999, Ulrich Windl wrote:
>Sep  3 07:00:45 kgate kernel: grow_inodes: inode-max limit reached
>Nov 11 07:01:51 kgate kernel: grow_inodes: inode-max limit reached
There is an inode leak in the VFS. I fixed it last week. My inode-max hard
limit showed the leak it to our eyes. In kernels _without_ the hard limit
(<2.2.14pre) the icache will silenty leak useful memory instead.
This is the fix.
	
ftp://ftp
.*.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/people/andrea/proposed/v2.2/2.2.13/inode-recycle-fixes.gz
(it will apply against most 2.2.x kernels)
Andrea
